<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 03 at 10:32PM EST  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...PATCHES OF DENSE FOG ACROSS THE WESTERN PIEDMONT...
Fog has developed across parts of the western Piedmont of North
Carolina, mainly west and north of the Charlotte metro area. The
fog has become locally dense in some places, especially around
rivers and low spots. If you are traveling about the region this
evening, you may encounter sharply reduced visibility to one-
quarter mile or less. Slow down and leave plenty of distance
between you and the cars ahead of you. The fog should move out as
a cold front crosses the region in the early morning hours.</description>
